</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC4FFC8FCF2FE511246C050" blockId="19.[826,1442,478,929]" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC4FFC8FCF2FE511348C2AC" box="[826,1027,479,500]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
This species is distinctive among species of the Apiciferum group and can be separated easily by the following characters: 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC4FFC8FB0CFD921215C169" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1220,1374,540,561]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC4FFC8FB0CFD921215C169" box="[1220,1374,540,561]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a black flagellomere and eye hairs, these being yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC4FFC8FC97FDD7148DC136" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[863,966,601,622]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC4FFC8FC97FDD7148DC136" box="[863,966,601,622]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC4FFC8FC13FDD713C8C136" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[987,1155,601,622]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC4FFC8FC13FDD713C8C136" box="[987,1155,601,622]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC4FFC8FB19FDD71238C136" baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1233,1395,601,622]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiciferum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC4FFC8FB19FDD71238C136" box="[1233,1395,601,622]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. apiciferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC4FFC8FA40FDD714FFC1D4" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC4FFC8FA40FDD714FFC1D4" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the abdominal tergites mainly yellow with conspicuous black stripes but 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC4FFC8FACCFD181225C1F3" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1284,1390,662,683]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC4FFC8FACCFD181225C1F3" box="[1284,1390,662,683]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC4FFC8FA40FD1814F0C192" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC4FFC8FA40FD1814F0C192" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC4FFC8FC34FD3B13D7C192" baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1020,1180,693,714]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiciferum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC4FFC8FC34FD3B13D7C192" box="[1020,1180,693,714]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. apiciferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have abdominal dark tergites without conspicuous stripes; 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC4FFC8FAC8FD5A12EAC1B0" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1280,1441,723,745]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC4FFC8FAC8FD5A12EAC1B0" box="[1280,1441,723,745]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the stylus with a tuft of long hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC4FFC8FC9BFC9F14BEC0F9" blockId="19.[826,1442,478,929]" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">
In early stages 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC4FFC8FBCBFC9F13D6C07D" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1027,1181,784,806]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC4FFC8FBCBFC9F13D6C07D" box="[1027,1181,784,806]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very distinctive and easily separated by the spicule pattern on the thorax. It is the only species of the Apiciferum group with spicules on the anterodorsal and lateral margins of the metathorax.
</paragraph>
